    "comment": "Rationale: Fig.1: \"Localization of Fz5 in the mouse hippocampus at different developmental stages\"\n- \"Consistent with its synaptic localization, Fz5 is present in synaptosomes isolated from adult mouse brain. Synaptophysin, N-type Ca2+ channel, PSD-95 and GluR1 were used as markers for different synaptic fractions. Fz5 is present in synaptosomes (S), and a pool of Fz5 is present in the synaptosomal membrane fraction (SMF) and also in the postsynaptic density (PSD) fraction (Fig. 1F). These results indicate that Fz5 is present at both pre- and postsynaptic sites.\"\n\nFig.2: \"Fz5 distribution in cultured hippocampal neurons\"\n- \"At 14 DIV, at the peak of synaptogenesis, 23% of sFz5 colocalizes with both synaptic markers but increases to 33% by 21 DIV (Fig. 2B,C)...Together, our data suggest that Fz5 is present at synaptic sites and that its synaptic localization increases during synapse formation.\". Experimental description: - \"Primary hippocampal cultures were prepared from embryonic day 18 (E18) Sprague-Dawley rat embryos ...\"",
